Monday, 20th December Lucky are the people of Yugoslavia and Somalia as the world s eyes rest on them. Condemned are the people of Juba It may be a blessing to die in front of a camera then at least the world will get to know about it. But it is painful to die or be killed, without anybody knowing it. Handwritten letter smuggled out of the besieged Southern Sudanese town of Juba, August 1992. WHILE YOU WERE SLEEPING FEATURED ARTICLES Video: Evita's Free Speech, Ep.69 Evita puts bad news where it belongs and pulls the chain BY PIETER-DIRK UYS BY PIETER-DIRK UYS Between frying pan and fire: Cape Town s shack dwellers BY MARELISE VAN DER MERWE BY MARELISE VAN DER MERWE OPINIONISTAS Spartacus lives! Remembering Kirk Douglas on his 100th birthday A column by KALIM RAJAB A column by KALIM RAJAB KALIM RAJAB A Common Thread A column by PAUL HOFFMAN A column by PAUL HOFFMAN PAUL HOFFMAN